From: Fernando Fernandez Mancera <fmancera@suse.de>
Date: Wed, 11 Jun 2025 11:00:56 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] kabi: add __nf_bridge_get_physindev() for kabi
References: bsc#1224726,CVE-2024-35839
Patch-Mainline: never, kabi fix

nf_bridge_get_physindev() arguments changes as now it receives an additional
struct net. In addition, nf_log_dump_packet_common() must propagate struct net
too. For kABI compliance reasons, change the names to
__nf_bridge_get_physindev() and __nf_log_dump_packet_common(). The original
functions were restored too.

The patch also adds back physindev field on nf_bridge_info and move physinif to
the bottom of the struct guarded by __GENKSYMS__.

Signed-off-by: Fernando Fernandez Mancera <fmancera@suse.de>
